{
  "text": "C values characteristic of ruminant milk, in order to demonstrate that Neolithic farmers in Britain were involved in dairying at least 7000 years ago. Different microbial taxa also have distinctive phospholipid fatty acids (PFLA), and by combining in situ 13 CO 2 stable isotope probing techniques at Sourhope with compound specific GC-C-IRMS, it was possible to identify microbial groups actively involved in the assimilation of root-derived carbon in limed grassland soils [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
